  <p>The AEM Screens is available by selecting the Adobe Experience Manager link (top left) and then Screens.</p> 
  <p>Alternatively, you can ï»¿go directly to: <a href="http://localhost:4502/screens.html/content/screens">http://localhost:4502/screens.html/content/screens</a></p> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/chlimage_1-47.png" /> 
  <p>Different projects could be differents brands, deployments, customers, and so on.</p> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/screen_shot_2018-08-23at105748am.png" /> 
  <note> 
   <p><strong>Navigation Tip:</strong></p> 
   <p>You can also use the cursor keys to navigate through different folders in AEM. Additionally, once you select a particular entity, hit spacebar to edit or view properties for that specific folder.</p> 
  </note> 
  <h2>Creating a New Screens Project</h2> 
  <p>Follow the steps below to create a new Screens project:</p> 
  <ol> 
   <li>Select <strong>Screens</strong> from the AEM dashboard.</li> 
   <li>Click <strong>Create </strong>--&amp;gt;<strong> Create Project </strong>and <strong>Create Screens Project</strong> wizard will open.</li> 
   <li>Select the <strong>Screens</strong> template and click <strong>Next</strong>.</li> 
   <li>Enter the properties (<strong>Title</strong> and <strong>Name</strong>) as required and click <strong>Create</strong>.</li> 
  </ol> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/player1.gif" /> 
  <note> 
   <p>By default, the initial structure will contain the <strong>Schedules</strong>, <strong>Locations</strong>, <strong>Applications</strong>, <strong>Channels</strong>, and <strong>Devices</strong> master pages, but this can be manually adjusted if needed. You can remove the options, if the available ones are not relevant to your project.</p> 
  </note> 
  <p>The project is created and it brings you back to the Screens Project console. You can now select your project.</p> 
  <p>In a project, there are four kind of folders, as shown in the figure below:</p> 
  <ul> 
   <li><strong>Schedules</strong></li> 
   <li><strong>Locations</strong></li> 
   <li><strong>Applications</strong></li> 
   <li><strong>Channels</strong></li> 
   <li><strong>Devices</strong></li> 
  </ul> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/screen_shot_2018-08-23at110114am.png" /> 
  <h3>Viewing Properties</h3> 
  <p>Once you create the Screens project, click <strong>Properties</strong> on the action bar to edit properties of an exiting AEM Screens project. </p> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/screen_shot_2018-08-23at110211am.png" /> 
  <p>The following options allow you to edit/change properties of your <em>DemoProject</em>.</p> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/screen_shot_2018-08-23at110409am.png" /> 
  <h3>Creating a Custom Folder</h3> 
  <p>You can also create your own custom folder under <strong>Schedules</strong>, <strong>Locations</strong>, <strong>Applications</strong>, <strong>Channels</strong>, and <strong>Devices</strong> master pages available in your project.</p> 
  <p>To create a custom folder:</p> 
  <ol> 
   <li>Select your project and click on <strong>Create</strong> next to plus icon in the action bar. </li> 
   <li>The <strong>Create</strong> wizard opens and select the appropriate option.</li> 
   <li>Click <strong>Next</strong>.</li> 
   <li>Enter the properties and click <strong>Create</strong>.</li> 
  </ol> 
  <p>The following steps show the creation of an applications folder to your <strong>Applications</strong> master page in <em>DemoProject</em>.</p> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/player2-1.gif" /> 
  <h3>The Next Steps</h3> 
  <p>Once you have created your own project, see <a href="../../screens/using/managing-channels.md"><strong>Channel Management</strong></a> to create and manage content in your channel.</p> 
  <p>Additionally, you can create your own schedule, application, location, or device.</p> 
